query.result:
112 He who seems so limber and who agrees,
113 singing, with him with the masculine nose,
114 of every valor carried the rope girded;

115 and if a king had remained after him,
116 the young man who sits behind him,
117 well would valor go from vessel to vessel,

118 which cannot be said of the other realms;
119 James and Frederick have the kingdoms;
120 of the inheritance, none possesses better.
